   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   VENNOCHI-COLUMN (Undated) _ Yes, Virginia, there is an Internet.
By Joan Vennochi.
</P>
<P>
   NYHAN-COLUMN (Undated) -- Bradford Washburn: At 89, the New
Englaner who has done it all. By David Nyhan.
</P>
<P>
   JACKSON-COLUMN (Undated) _ The MCAS could become a tool more for
punishing students and blaming parents. By Derrick Jackson.
</P>
<P>
   (Eds.: Alex Beam's column is unavailable today.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
