<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hello, I must be going
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Even for a guy who has played with seven NHL teams in
11 seasons, this season qualifies as a bizarre one for Rick
Tabaracci. The veteran goalie went a month into the season before
being signed by the Thrashers as an unrestricted free agent. He was
assigned to Orlando (IHL), called up as an injury replacement,
started one game against Dallas, was sent back down and then was
traded to Colorado. The Avalanche needed a veteran goalie for the
expansion draft in June. But NHL rules stipulate that the goalie
must have played at least 25 games over the last two years, and
Tabaracci was at 24 (23 with Washington, one with Atlanta). So the
Avs recalled Tabaracci from the minors, started him against
Carolina, won 4-2 and now might send him back down. ``To be honest,
I don't know what the plan is for me,'' Tabaracci said. ``I
maintain one thing: If you play well, you are going to play. I
believe I can still help a lot of NHL clubs. Hopefully, it's this
one, but if it's not, it's another one.'' Columbus or Minnesota,
for example.
</P>
<P>
   FACEOFF: TERRY MURRAY
</P>
<P>
   Coach, Florida Panthers
</P>
<P>
   _ Update: Blew a third-period lead for the first time this
season in a 3-3 tie with Atlanta. Still has the inside track to win
the Southeast Division, despite the recent loss of goalie Trevor
Kidd, who might require season-ending surgery on his dislocated
shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   _ On preventing a letdown by his players during Kidd's absence:
``When it first happened, we addressed it with the players to make
sure the mental slump didn't creep in. We didn't want them to feel
sorry for themselves, just because we were losing a key player on
the hockey club. I think talking about it was the right thing to
do. We have to keep going forward and have confidence in (backup
Mikhail) Shtalenkov. We've handled it pretty well.''
</P>
<P>
   _ On some recent losses: ``Anytime we lose a game, even though
we respect the other teams, we believe it's because of our own
performance. We're trying to get back to the playoffs. We believe
we can play with the top teams in the league. But when you're not
prepared mentally, any team can take it to you. Then, when you
start to think it's time to turn the table around, sometimes it's
too late. That's what's happened in all the games we've lost this
year.
</P>
<P>
   _ On acquiring a replacement for Kidd: ``We're still in the
process of making phone calls and finding what the heck is out
there to see if we can make a deal to give us the tandem that we're
going to need.''
</P>
