forgotten him for it. It was how her husband unwound after coming
home from another Christmas tour to somewhere in the world where
America's soldiers needed a shot in the arm. ``It was the part that
gave him more satisfaction than anything, meeting the men and
seeing them smile,'' she said. ``For a few hours, he replaced their
fear and loneliness with laughs. And now, at 96, Bob Hope says
