   (NYT15) NEW YORK -- Dec. 24, 1999 -- NY-HOSPITALS-Y2K-2 -- June
Vetter, a patient care technician, left, is helped into a level 2
biohazard suit at the Maimonides Medical Center in Brooklyn earlier
this week. Almost two dozen doctors, nurses and other hospital
staff members here have taken part in a two-day rigorous training
program in protecting themselves and treating victims of a chemical
weapons attack, should they be wheeled into their emergency room on
New Year's Eve. (Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) NEW YORK -- Dec. 24, 1999 -- NY-HOSPITALS-Y2K-1 -- June
Vetter, a patient care technician in a level 2 biohazard suit, sits
in a decontamination shower stall at the Maimonides Medical Center
in Brooklyn earlier this week. Facing the last New Year's eve of
the century, which some security officials have cited as a possible
key evening for terrorism, hospitals like Maimonides are beefing up
their procedures. (Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) NEW YORK -- Dec. 24, 1999 -- NY-CREW-ASSESS -- Rudy
Crew, the outgoing chancellor of the New York City Board of
Education, walks his dog Chance outside his apartment in Brooklyn
Heights on Friday. Thursday's vote by the board not to renew Crew's
contract ended his sometimes turbulent term as the head of the
nation's largest public school system. The city has had 10
chancellors in the last 30 years, with seven of them ousted or
pressured to resign. (Aaron Lee Fineman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) ISTANBUL -- Dec. 24, 1999 -- TURKEY-SULTAN -- A young
Turkish couple look at a portrait of Turkey's most famous sultan,
