   (NYT6) BUJUMBURA, Burundi -- Dec. 24, 1999 -- BURUNDI-CAMPS-3 --
Children stands in front of under construction in a camp called
Mukonko II, on a hillside southeast of Bujumbura where 5,800 people
now live. In the last three months, Burundi's government has herded
350,000 people, mostly poor farmers, from their homes into grubby
new villages atop the hills that encircle Bujumbura. The camps are
supposed to be temporary but a permanence is settling in. (Ian
Fisher/The New York Times)
</P>
