<P>
   (NYT2) BETHLEHEM, West Bank P Dec. 24, 1999 --
CHRISTMAS-BETHLEHEM-2 -- A Palestinian in Turkish dress leans on
his staff as he waits to lead alterboys and clergymen during a
procession which escorts the Latin Patriarch into the Church of the
Nativity, seen in the background, on Friday, Christmas Eve. The
ancient church was erected over the site traditionally believed to
be the birthplace of Jesus. The Turkish dress tradition dates back
to the time of the Ottoman Empire rule in Palestine. (Rina
Castelnuovo/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) BETHLEHEM, West Bank P Dec. 24, 1999 --
